                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                <head>No. 270.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Cadwalader</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Nicholas Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-08-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 1, 1874</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 689.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch of the 15th ultimo, No. 4,
                    inclosing, with extracts from the German press, a copy of your note of the 14th
                    ultimo to Prince Bismarck, congratulating him upon his escape from
                    assassination, has been received.</p>
                <p>Your action in congratulating the prince, as “communicated by telegraph, has
                    already been approved in No. 684, trom the Department.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN L. CADWALADER,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
